Interface Services

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ServicesTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ServicesStub

    public interface Services
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, ServicesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Services interface manages the Key Provider Service instances a Trusted Cluster is configured to use. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

      • list

        Services.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String cluster)
        Returns basic information about all configured Key Provider Service instances used by this cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        basic information about all configured Key Provider Service instances used by this cluster

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        instance of Services.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if the cluster ID is invalid.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires TrustedAdmin.ReadTrustedHosts.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the parameter cluster requires System.View.

      • create

        Services.CreateInvocation create(java.lang.String cluster,
                                 ServicesTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Configures the cluster to use a the given registered Key Provider Service. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.

        Invocation Result:
        ID of the configured Key Provider Service instance. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.kms.Service.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - Describes the registered instance of the Key Provider Service
        Returns:
        instance of Services.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        AlreadyExists - if the Key Provider Service is already configured for this cluster
        Error - for any other error.
        InvalidArgument - if the CreateSpec is not valid.
        NotFound - if the cluster ID is not valid.
        UnableToAllocateResource - if all the hosts in the cluster do not have VMware vSphere Trust Authority enabled license.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.

      • delete

        Services.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String cluster,
                                 java.lang.String service)
        Removes the Key Provider Service instance from the configuration of the given cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0.
        Parameters:
        cluster - the unique ID of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        service - the registered Key Provider Service instance unique identifier. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.kms.Service.
        Returns:
        instance of Services.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        NotFound - if the Key Provider Service instance or the cluster are not found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
